    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "WATER EVACUATION\nAdult\nAssess outside conditions at Emergency Exits.\nIf fire, water above the door sill or dangerous debris exists,\nDO NOT OPEN!\nProceed to another exit.\n5\nINFLATE\nUPON\nEXITING\nChild\nInfant or small child under 35lbs\nFinal assembly of this airplane was completed in France.\nCopyright 2009 SAFEAIR, INC. 360/753-0092 www.safeair-usa.com Reproduction, all or in part, without written permission of\nSafeair, Inc. is prohibited. Violations are subject to prosecution under Federal Copyright Laws. P/N B20001 Rev. C 11/13 Type AA1A",
      "A330 FOR YOUR SAFETY\nHAWA!!AN\nHAWAIIAN\n- AIRLINES.—\nPOUR VOTRE SÉCURITÉ\nFÜR IHRE SICHERHEIT\nPARA SU SEQURIDAD\nMO LOU SAOGALEMU\nPLEASE DO NOT REMOVE CARD FROM AIRCRAFT\nFederal Regulations require that all passengers comply with any illuminated sign,\nprinted placard and/or verbal safety instructions given by a crewmember.\nUnder federal law, no person may assault, threaten, intimidate or interfere with a crewmember in the performance\nof their duties aboard an aircraft under operation. Federal law permits penalties for crew interference to include\nsubstantial fines (up to $25,000), imprisonment or both."
